      "rationale": "Three-level mesh refinement study performed (2.1M, 8.4M, 33.6M elements) with GCI reported for NIH at all operating points. GCI below 5% on fine mesh. Discretization error adequately characterized but study was performed under the 2024-q3-build-2 configuration. Achieved level 3 against required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions must match COU operating envelope within stated uncertainty bounds. Blood analog fluid properties must be documented and traceable.",
      "rationale": "FDA PIV data used glycerol-water analog (40% glycerol by mass) at 22°C. COU requires predictions for human blood at 37°C across physiological viscosity range. Fluid property mismatch introduces unquantified bias in hemolysis predictions. Achieved level 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric (e.g., validation metric of ASME V&V 20) must be computed for primary QoI. Uncertainty in both simulation and experiment must be propagated into the comparison.",
      "rationale": "Mean absolute error computed for velocity fields; NIH compared at five operating points. Experimental uncertainty not fully propagated into comparison metric. No formal ASME V&V 20 validation metric computed. Achieved level 2 against required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation QoI must be the same as or directly predictive of the COU QoI (absolute NIH). Intermediate QoI such as velocity fields must be demonstrated to be predictive of hemolysis index.",
      "rationale": "Velocity field validation is an intermediate QoI. The link from velocity field accuracy to hemolysis index prediction accuracy is model-form dependent and not independently validated. Direct NIH validation dataset is limited to five operating points with high experimental scatter. Achieved level 2 against required level 5."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation geometry, operating conditions, and fluid must match or bracket the COU device and conditions. Extrapolation distance must be quantified.",
      "rationale": "Validation performed on FDA generic pump geometry, not the specific VAD device geometry of the COU. Operating speed range partially overlaps COU envelope. Blood analog fluid used in experiments rather than human blood. Substantial extrapolation required. Achieved level 2 against required level 5."
