      "acceptanceCriteria": "Sensitivity of hemolysis predictions to turbulence model choice must be quantified. Alternative hemolysis correlations must be assessed. Model form uncertainty must be propagated into final NIH uncertainty band.",
      "rationale": "SST k-omega selected without comparison to alternative turbulence models (e.g., RSM, LES) for hemolysis-relevant flow features. Giersiepen hemolysis correlation used without assessment of Bludszuweit or Taskin alternatives. Model form uncertainty not propagated. Critical gap at MRL 5. Achieved level 1."
