      "acceptanceCriteria": "Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification must be performed on all uncertain input parameters. Input distributions must be justified from literature or measurement. Sensitivity indices must identify dominant inputs.",
      "rationale": "Monte Carlo UQ performed on 6 input parameters (viscosity, density, hemolysis correlation exponents, inlet velocity profile). Input distributions based on literature ranges. Sobol sensitivity indices computed; hemolysis exponent alpha identified as dominant. However, geometric manufacturing tolerances not included in UQ. Achieved level 2 against required level 5."
    },
