    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/morrison-cou2-vad-decision-2026q1",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment team accepted the package for submission based on the completeness of the 13-factor assessment and the availability of Monte Carlo UQ results. All seven assessed factors show achieved levels below required levels, and six factors remain not-assessed epistemic gaps. The team noted that the primary validation evidence (PIV velocity comparison and NIH comparison) was generated under solver build 2024-q3-build-2, which corresponds to the current model of record build 2026-q1-build-7 per internal release documentation — however, this equivalence was asserted verbally and not confirmed by re-running validation cases under the updated build. The package is accepted for regulatory submission with the understanding that validation evidence is considered current.",
